transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, this is Viagra.

Speaker 2: Hello?

Speaker 1: Hello, how are we doing, sir?

Speaker 2: Yes, I'm trying to cancel my subscription.

Speaker 1: Okay, let me pull the prescription.

Speaker 2: Mr. McNamara?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: Yes, so I see you have a prescription from Dr. Tabrik for Viagra, 100 milligrams,

Speaker 1: and you initially ordered, I think, 40 tablets.

Speaker 2: You can pause the order if you don't need it.

Speaker 1: I can advise the pharmacy to stop the initial order and prescription, and you can get, you know,

Speaker 2: lesser quantity, maybe 10 pills once or twice a year or, you know.

Speaker 1: No, it doesn't do nothing for me.

Speaker 2: I do not need it.

Speaker 1: Oh, okay, okay.

Speaker 2: That was your first time taking Viagra?

Speaker 1: Yeah, I've taken it before, but I thought it was a new pill that was different,

Speaker 2: but it doesn't do anything different for me, so I don't need it.

Speaker 1: Okay, okay, got you.

Speaker 2: And you try Cialis?

Speaker 1: Is Cialis better for you, or you never tried it?

Speaker 2: No, no, no.

Speaker 1: I'm a diabetic.

Speaker 2: This does not do nothing for me.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Okay?

Speaker 1: Yeah, I mean, we have diabetic patients at work,

Speaker 2: so we usually ask questions to try to, you know, get you some things better, you know.

Speaker 1: Okay, I just need to cancel it.

Speaker 2: I don't need that no more.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: All right, I'm canceling the doctor prescription.

Speaker 1: I was trying to evaluate with you if we could have you maybe trying a sample.

Speaker 2: Who could be better?

Speaker 1: You declined.

Speaker 2: No, no, I don't want to try nothing else.

Speaker 1: No, I'm done.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: You also, Mr. McNamara, everything has been canceled.

Speaker 1: Okay, thank you.

Speaker 2: You're welcome.

Speaker 1: All right, have a good day.

Speaker 2: You too.

Speaker 1: All right, bye.

Speaker 2: Bye.
